  "prompt": "What is the legal framework surrounding money laundering?",
  "response": "The legal framework surrounding money laundering involves multiple international and national regulations designed to prevent, detect, and prosecute financial crimes. Here are key components:\n\n1. International Regulations\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention Against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n- Egmont Group international cooperation standards\n\n2. National Legislation\n- Bank Secrecy Act (BSA) in the United States\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) laws\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) requirements\n- Suspicious Activity Reporting (SAR) protocols\n\n3. Key Legal Elements\n- Criminal penalties for money laundering\n- Asset seizure and forfeiture\n- Mandatory financial institution reporting\n- Transaction monitoring requirements\n- Cross-border financial transaction tracking\n\n4. Regulatory Compliance\n- Financial institutions must implement AML programs\n- Regular risk assessments\n- Employee training\n- Internal control mechanisms\n- Reporting suspicious transactions\n\n5. Enforcement Mechanisms\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Civil penalties\n- Financial institution sanctions\n- International law enforcement cooperation\n\nThe framework aims to disrupt criminal financial activities and prevent proceeds from illegal activities entering legitimate financial systems.",
